race.description: Spelling At Coolmore Mt White Handicap (Bm94)
race.comment: LULUMON (10) underrated mare who returns from a lengthy break. Has solid fresh credentials and gets the right set-up on the limit. Closed strongly in her second trial and look for her to launch late. SPRING LEE (7) held her own in Group company last time in and looks to have strengthened further over the break. Has the speed to get across from the awkward draw and looked to have plenty up the sleeve in both trials. Respect. CELUI (6) resumes. Failed to handle the heavy conditions when seventh in the LR Hawkesbury Gold Rush last May. Primed with the two good trial wins and gets every chance from the draw. THE BLACK CLOUD (3) bounced off her narrow second in the G3 The Warra, with a well-deserved victory in the LR Bribie Hcp over 1000m at Eagle Farm eight weeks ago. Kept up to the mark with the two trials and gets every chance. CHINQUI (8) goes well at this trip and capable of bouncing back after disappointing when eighth at the Gold Coast. Well drawn with the claim. Place best.
